<paragraph blockId="28.[164,779,1728,1903]" lastBlockId="28.[826,1441,871,1321]" pageId="28" pageNumber="662">
<emphasis box="[164,398,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="662">Emended diagnosis:</emphasis>
The following character combination is diagnostic for 
<emphasis box="[436,577,1758,1780]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="662">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perez-Miles &amp; Locht" authorityYear="2003" box="[436,573,1758,1780]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hemirrhagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="662" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocellatus">H. ocellatus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Male palpal bulb with slender embolus similar in length to tegulum, 
<collectionCode box="[164,197,1820,1841]" country="France" name="Museum national d'Histoire Naturelle, Laboratiore de Paleontologie" pageId="28" pageNumber="662">SA</collectionCode>
ends at embolus retrolateral face (
<figureCitation box="[628,766,1819,1841]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="18.[164,243,736,755]" captionTargetBox="[396,1207,205,699]" captionTargetId="figure-162@18.[387,1219,197,706]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 18. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 4457, left palpal bulb: A, retrolateral view. B, prolateral view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. Abbreviations: SA, subapical keel; VG, ventral groove. Scale bar = 1 mm." pageId="28" pageNumber="662">Fig. 18A, D</figureCitation>
); VG shallow (
<figureCitation box="[337,435,1850,1872]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="18.[164,243,736,755]" captionTargetBox="[396,1207,205,699]" captionTargetId="figure-162@18.[387,1219,197,706]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 18. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 4457, left palpal bulb: A, retrolateral view. B, prolateral view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. Abbreviations: SA, subapical keel; VG, ventral groove. Scale bar = 1 mm." pageId="28" pageNumber="662">Fig. 18B</figureCitation>
). Embolus strongly curved retrolaterally on distal half (
<figureCitation box="[494,627,1881,1903]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="18.[164,243,736,755]" captionTargetBox="[396,1207,205,699]" captionTargetId="figure-162@18.[387,1219,197,706]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 18. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 4457, left palpal bulb: A, retrolateral view. B, prolateral view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. Abbreviations: SA, subapical keel; VG, ventral groove. Scale bar = 1 mm." pageId="28" pageNumber="662">Fig. 18C, D</figureCitation>
). Metatarsus I straight (
<figureCitation box="[951,1053,871,893]" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="17.[144,223,1435,1454]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-108@17.[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 17. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 4457. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, opisthosoma, ventral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, sternum. G, tibial apophyses, ventral view. H, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. I, labial and maxillary cuspules. J, metatarsus I, prolateral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–C), 1 mm (F–J), 0.5 mm (D, E)." pageId="28" pageNumber="662">Fig. 17H</figureCitation>
). Ocular tubercle slightly reduced and eyes normally developed; periocular pigmentation complete (
<figureCitation box="[947,1049,932,954]" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="17.[144,223,1435,1454]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-108@17.[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 17. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 4457. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, opisthosoma, ventral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, sternum. G, tibial apophyses, ventral view. H, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. I, labial and maxillary cuspules. J, metatarsus I, prolateral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–C), 1 mm (F–J), 0.5 mm (D, E)." pageId="28" pageNumber="662">Figs 17E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1066,1114,932,954]" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="18.[164,243,1363,1382]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,861,1333]" captionTargetId="figure-201@18.[323,1283,861,1333]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 19. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, holotype female LAAH. A, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). B, opisthosoma, dorsal view. C, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. D, spermathecae, ventral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A, B), 1 mm (D), 0.5 mm (C)." pageId="28" pageNumber="662">19C</figureCitation>
). Tarsi 
<collectionCode box="[1208,1226,932,953]" pageId="28" pageNumber="662">II</collectionCode>
– 
<collectionCode box="[1240,1269,932,953]" pageId="28" pageNumber="662">IV</collectionCode>
with scopulae divided. Six to ten labial cuspules (
<figureCitation box="[1251,1349,962,985]" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="17.[144,223,1435,1454]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-108@17.[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 17. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 4457. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, opisthosoma, ventral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, sternum. G, tibial apophyses, ventral view. H, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. I, labial and maxillary cuspules. J, metatarsus I, prolateral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–C), 1 mm (F–J), 0.5 mm (D, E)." pageId="28" pageNumber="662">Fig. 17F</figureCitation>
). Males with rounded sternum (
<figureCitation box="[1101,1234,993,1015]" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="17.[144,223,1435,1454]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-108@17.[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 17. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 4457. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, opisthosoma, ventral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, sternum. G, tibial apophyses, ventral view. H, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. I, labial and maxillary cuspules. J, metatarsus I, prolateral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–C), 1 mm (F–J), 0.5 mm (D, E)." pageId="28" pageNumber="662">Fig. 17B, G</figureCitation>
). Urticating setae arranged in two dorsal paramedian patches; ovalshaped, yellowish-orange in colour, and well-defined margins (
<figureCitation box="[954,1057,1085,1107]" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="17.[144,223,1435,1454]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-108@17.[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 17. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 4457. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, opisthosoma, ventral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, sternum. G, tibial apophyses, ventral view. H, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. I, labial and maxillary cuspules. J, metatarsus I, prolateral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–C), 1 mm (F–J), 0.5 mm (D, E)." pageId="28" pageNumber="662">Figs 17C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1087,1135,1085,1107]" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="18.[164,243,1363,1382]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,861,1333]" captionTargetId="figure-201@18.[323,1283,861,1333]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 19. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, holotype female LAAH. A, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). B, opisthosoma, dorsal view. C, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. D, spermathecae, ventral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A, B), 1 mm (D), 0.5 mm (C)." pageId="28" pageNumber="662">19B</figureCitation>
). Spermathecae paired, slightly fused; receptacles slender throughout their length; strongly curved outwards from the middle (
<figureCitation box="[834,935,1176,1199]" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="18.[164,243,1363,1382]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,861,1333]" captionTargetId="figure-201@18.[323,1283,861,1333]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 19. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, holotype female LAAH. A, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). B, opisthosoma, dorsal view. C, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. D, spermathecae, ventral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A, B), 1 mm (D), 0.5 mm (C)." pageId="28" pageNumber="662">Fig. 19D</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perez-Miles &amp; Locht" authorityYear="2003" box="[960,1223,1176,1197]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hemirrhagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="662" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ocellatus">
<emphasis box="[960,1223,1176,1197]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="662">Hemirrhagus ocellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from most 
<taxonomicName box="[826,1072,1207,1229]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hemirrhagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="662" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[826,978,1207,1228]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="662">Hemirrhagus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by the urticating setae being arranged in two dorsal paramedian patches and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perez-Miles &amp; Locht" authorityYear="2003" box="[887,1010,1268,1290]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Hemirrhagus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="28" pageNumber="662" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gertschi">
<emphasis box="[887,1010,1268,1290]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="662">H. gertschi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the periocular pigmentation being complete.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[826,1441,1360,1902]" pageId="28" pageNumber="662">
<emphasis box="[826,962,1361,1382]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="662">Description:</emphasis>
Male: body length (not including chelicerae and spinnerets) 16.70, carapace: 6.58 long, 5.59 wide. Caput not markedly elevated; fovea recurved, 0.88 wide (
<figureCitation box="[1072,1171,1452,1474]" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="17.[144,223,1435,1454]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-108@17.[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 17. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 4457. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, opisthosoma, ventral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, sternum. G, tibial apophyses, ventral view. H, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. I, labial and maxillary cuspules. J, metatarsus I, prolateral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–C), 1 mm (F–J), 0.5 mm (D, E)." pageId="28" pageNumber="662">Fig. 17A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[826,1441,1360,1902]" lastBlockId="29.[144,759,198,1474]" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="663" pageId="28" pageNumber="662">
Eyes: anterior eye row procurved, posterior eye row recurved. Periocular pigmentation complete. All eyes normally developed. Eye sizes and interocular distances: AME 0.28; ALE 0.30; PME 0.15; PLE 0.25; AME–AME 0.020; AME–ALE 0.025; PME–PME 0.48; PME–PLE 0.038; ALE–PLP 0.10. Ocular tubercle slightly reduced, width 1.15; length 0.73; clypeus lacking (
<figureCitation box="[929,1028,1697,1719]" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="17.[144,223,1435,1454]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-108@17.[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 17. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 4457. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, opisthosoma, ventral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, sternum. G, tibial apophyses, ventral view. H, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. I, labial and maxillary cuspules. J, metatarsus I, prolateral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–C), 1 mm (F–J), 0.5 mm (D, E)." pageId="28" pageNumber="662">Fig. 17E</figureCitation>
). Labium: length 0.83; width 1.33; with 10 cuspules. Maxilla inner corner with approximately 82 cuspules (
<figureCitation box="[1072,1170,1758,1780]" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="17.[144,223,1435,1454]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-108@17.[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 17. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 4457. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, opisthosoma, ventral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, sternum. G, tibial apophyses, ventral view. H, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. I, labial and maxillary cuspules. J, metatarsus I, prolateral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–C), 1 mm (F–J), 0.5 mm (D, E)." pageId="28" pageNumber="662">Fig. 17F</figureCitation>
). Cheliceral promargin with 11 teeth (proximal to distal: first small, secondthird large, fourth small, fifth-sixth medium, seventhninth large, tenth medium, eleventh small). Sternum length 2.97. Sigillae semicircular, second, third, and fourth pairs hardly visible; fourth pair once its length from the margin (
<figureCitation box="[354,489,228,251]" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="17.[144,223,1435,1454]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-108@17.[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 17. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 4457. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, opisthosoma, ventral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, sternum. G, tibial apophyses, ventral view. H, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. I, labial and maxillary cuspules. J, metatarsus I, prolateral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–C), 1 mm (F–J), 0.5 mm (D, E)." pageId="29" pageNumber="663">Fig. 17B, G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[144,759,198,1474]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">
Leg formula: 
<collectionCode box="[323,351,259,280]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">IV</collectionCode>
, I, 
<collectionCode box="[387,419,259,280]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">III</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode box="[431,454,259,280]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">II</collectionCode>
. Length of legs and palpal segments (femur, patella, tibia, metatarsus, tarsus, total): I: 6.41, 3.38, 5.50, 5.14, 4.05, 24.48. 
<collectionCode box="[612,635,321,342]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">II</collectionCode>
: 5.53, 3.09, 4.99, 4.82, 3.91, 22.34. 
<collectionCode box="[408,441,351,372]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">III</collectionCode>
: 5.70, 2.57, 4.61, 5.64, 3.98, 22.50. 
<collectionCode box="[218,248,382,403]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">IV</collectionCode>
: 7.28, 3.01, 6.18, 7.68, 4.60, 28.75. Palp: 4.65, 2.42, 3.66, -, 1.95, 12.68. Spinnerets: 
<collectionCode box="[556,614,412,433]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/9hjz-r0xi" name="Peabody Essex Museum" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">PMS</collectionCode>
, 0.7 long, 0.4 apart; PLS, 1.0 basal, 0.7 middle, 1.1 distal.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[144,759,198,1474]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">
Scopulae: tarsi I– 
<collectionCode box="[375,404,474,495]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">IV</collectionCode>
densely scopulate, 
<collectionCode box="[637,659,474,495]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">II</collectionCode>
, divided by a row of soft setae, 
<collectionCode box="[408,438,504,525]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">III</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[499,527,504,525]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">IV</collectionCode>
divided by a row of hard setae. Metatarsi I– 
<collectionCode box="[439,458,535,556]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">II</collectionCode>
scopulate on distal twothirds; 
<collectionCode box="[228,258,565,586]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">III</collectionCode>
scopulate on distal third, and 
<collectionCode box="[615,643,565,586]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">IV</collectionCode>
scopulate on distal fifth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[144,759,198,1474]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">
Tibia I with two apophyses, which do not originate from a common base, Pap reduced with one large spinose seta on ventral face, spinose seta bent apically and exceeds the apex of Pap; Rap narrow with one large spinose seta on dorsal face, the spinose seta exceeds the apex of Rap (
<figureCitation box="[456,578,779,801]" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="17.[144,223,1435,1454]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-108@17.[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 17. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 4457. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, opisthosoma, ventral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, sternum. G, tibial apophyses, ventral view. H, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. I, labial and maxillary cuspules. J, metatarsus I, prolateral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–C), 1 mm (F–J), 0.5 mm (D, E)." pageId="29" pageNumber="663">Fig. 17I, J</figureCitation>
). Metatarsus I straight (
<figureCitation box="[253,355,810,832]" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="17.[144,223,1435,1454]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-108@17.[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 17. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 4457. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, opisthosoma, ventral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, sternum. G, tibial apophyses, ventral view. H, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. I, labial and maxillary cuspules. J, metatarsus I, prolateral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–C), 1 mm (F–J), 0.5 mm (D, E)." pageId="29" pageNumber="663">Fig. 17H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[144,759,198,1474]" box="[168,485,840,862]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">Stridulatory setae: lacking.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[144,759,198,1474]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">
Legs and palpi LSC in: palp trochanter retrolateral face, femur prolateral and retrolateral faces; leg I coxa retrolateral face, trochanter prolateral face, femur prolateral face; leg 
<collectionCode box="[439,459,963,984]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">II</collectionCode>
trochanter prolateral face and femur prolateral face proximally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[144,759,198,1474]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">
Chaetotaxy (left side): femora I 1p; 
<collectionCode box="[576,596,1024,1045]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">II</collectionCode>
1p; 
<collectionCode box="[647,677,1024,1045]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">III</collectionCode>
2p, 2r; 
<collectionCode box="[144,172,1055,1076]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">IV</collectionCode>
1p, 2r; palp 1p; patellae none; tibiae I 2p, 7v, 3r; 
<collectionCode box="[738,758,1055,1076]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">II</collectionCode>
2p, 8v; 
<collectionCode box="[225,255,1085,1106]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">III</collectionCode>
2p, 12v, 2r; 
<collectionCode box="[391,419,1085,1106]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">IV</collectionCode>
2p, 12v, 6r; palp 1p, 7v; metatarsi I 6v; 
<collectionCode box="[265,285,1116,1137]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">II</collectionCode>
1p, 6v; 
<collectionCode box="[378,408,1116,1137]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">III</collectionCode>
4p, 14v, 3r; 
<collectionCode box="[552,580,1116,1137]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">IV</collectionCode>
1d, 5p, 16v, 5r.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[144,759,198,1474]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">
Palp: embolus slender, similar in length to tegulum, 
<collectionCode box="[144,177,1177,1198]" country="France" name="Museum national d'Histoire Naturelle, Laboratiore de Paleontologie" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">SA</collectionCode>
ends at embolus retrolateral face; ventral groove shallow. Embolus strongly curved retrolaterally on distal half. Apex of embolus strongly curved ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[152,284,1269,1291]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="18.[164,243,736,755]" captionTargetBox="[396,1207,205,699]" captionTargetId="figure-162@18.[387,1219,197,706]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 18. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 4457, left palpal bulb: A, retrolateral view. B, prolateral view. C, dorsal view. D, ventral view. Abbreviations: SA, subapical keel; VG, ventral groove. Scale bar = 1 mm." pageId="29" pageNumber="663">Fig. 18A–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[144,759,198,1474]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">
<materialsCitation collectionCode="VI" pageId="29" pageNumber="663" specimenCount="1">
Urticating setae: 
<typeStatus box="[373,422,1300,1321]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">type</typeStatus>
<collectionCode box="[432,460,1300,1321]" country="Norway" name="Mykotektet, National Veterinary Institute" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">VI</collectionCode>
arranged in two dorsolateral patches, oval-shaped, yellowish-orange in colour and well-defined margins (
<figureCitation box="[456,555,1360,1382]" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="17.[144,223,1435,1454]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-108@17.[303,1263,194,1405]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 17. Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, male CNAN 4457. A, carapace, dorsal view. B, prosoma, ventral view showing the retrolateral projection of the coxa (RP) on coxae of all legs (arrows show this feature only on coxa of third and fourth legs). C, opisthosoma, dorsal view. D, opisthosoma, ventral view. E, ocular tubercle, dorsal view. F, sternum. G, tibial apophyses, ventral view. H, tibial apophyses, prolateral view. I, labial and maxillary cuspules. J, metatarsus I, prolateral view. Scale bars = 2 mm (A–C), 1 mm (F–J), 0.5 mm (D, E)." pageId="29" pageNumber="663">Fig. 17C</figureCitation>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[144,759,198,1474]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">Colour pattern: in ethanol specimen colour is yellowish. Live specimens are black, with urticating setae patches yellowish-orange.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[144,759,1513,1658]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">
<emphasis box="[144,537,1513,1534]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">Distribution and natural history:</emphasis>
Known only from Cueva de la Peña Blanca, Valle de Bravo, 
<collectingRegion country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="29" pageNumber="663">Estado de México</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[281,372,1574,1596]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[164,243,1137,1156]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,196,1107]" captionTargetId="figure-206@4.[323,1283,196,1107]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. A–C, Hemirrhagus spp. habitus; D–K, habitat. A, B, Hemirrhagus embolulatus sp. nov., A, holotype male CNAN-T0774, in life, B, paratype female CNAN-T0775, in life; C, Hemirrhagus valdezi sp. nov., paratype female CNAN-T0780, in life; D, Cueva de la Peña Blanca entrance, type locality of Hemirrhagus ocellatus; E, 4 km west of Puerto de la Soledad, pine forest, type locality of Hemirrhagus franckei sp. nov.; F, Bosque del ajusco, pine forest, locality of Hemirrhagus chilango; G, Valle de los fantasmas, oak forest on the road to Cueva de la Laguna, type locality of Hemirrhagus elliotti; H, Cueva de los Potrerillos entrance, type locality of Hemirrhagus stygius; I, Paradero Puerta del Sol, pine forest, locality of Hemirrhagus benzaa sp. nov.; J, Omiltemi, tropical forest-pine forest ecotone, type locality of H. embolulatus sp. nov.; K, El punto, type locality of Hemirrhagus eros. Photos: A: M. Gamache; B, E, I, K: E. Goyer; C: L. Vazquez; D, F, J: J. Mendoza; G, H: J. Cruz." pageId="29" pageNumber="663">Figs 2D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[389,420,1575,1597]" captionStart="Figure 49" captionStartId="52.[164,243,1007,1026]" captionTargetBox="[172,1436,200,970]" captionTargetId="figure-347@52.[164,1444,195,977]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Figure 49. Known distribution of Hemirrhagus mitchelli (Gertsch, 1982), Hemirrhagus puebla (Gertsch, 1982), Hemirrhagus ocellatus Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, Hemirrhagus gertschi Pérez-Miles &amp; Locht, 2003, Hemirrhagus valdezi sp. nov., Hemirrhagus pernix (Ausserer, 1875), Hemirrhagus franckei sp. nov., Hemirrhagus reddelli (Gertsch, 1973), Hemirrhagus benzaa sp. nov., and Hemirrhagus guichi sp. nov." pageId="29" pageNumber="663">49</figureCitation>
). The specimens were found under rocks and walking on the cave walls at a depth of 
<specimenCount box="[174,237,1636,1657]" pageId="29" pageNumber="663" type="generic">
<quantity box="[174,233,1636,1657]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="29" pageNumber="663" unit="m" value="30.0">30 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
